"1360","1260":"1260","1270":"1270","1291":"1291","1306":"1306","Over Walton Manor, Cheshire, England":"Over, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Walcot, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Walcot, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","Walcot, Shropshire, England":"Walcot, Shropshire, England","Weobley Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Weobley, Herefordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Walton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of numerous places called Walton, which are named with Old English <i>walh</i> ‘foreigner, Briton, serf’ (genitive plural <i>wala</i>), <i>wald</i> ‘woodland’, <i>wall</i> ‘wall’, or <i>wælla</i> ‘well, spring, stream’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’.","History: George Walton (1741–1804) signed the Declaration of Independence. He was born in Prince Edward County, VA, whither his grandfather had emigrated from England in 1682. He moved to Savannah, GA, and became governor of GA and a prominent jurist."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Idonea","type":"FIRST","meanings":["An old baptismal name derived from Latin idoneus, fit, meet, proper."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of any of the given names beginning with the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Idonea de Walton was born in 1240, in Over, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Thomas de Walton and Mrs Thomas Walton. She married Simon de Marbury in 1259, in Weobley, Herefordshire, England. They were the parents of at least 5 sons."},"et":{"1240–":"1240–Surnud","1240–Female":"1240–Surnud","1246–1306":"1246–1306","1234–Ma